==English==

===Etymology===
From {{w|Blame Canada}}, a song from the satirical 1999 film ''[[w:South Park: Bigger, Longer & Uncut|South Park: Bigger, Longer & Uncut]]''.

===Verb===
{{infl|en|verb|head=to [[blame]] [[Canada]]}}

# {{US|idiom}} A [[catch phrase]] for shifting attention away from a serious social issue by laying [[responsibility]] with Canada.
